§ specs/52_COHERENCE_AXES_13 · 13-axes coherence-engine port-and-integration
  ← source : Labyrinth-of-Apocalypse/systems/coherence_engine.csl (existing-pre-authored)
  ← target : substrate-render + KAN-bias + procgen-pipeline integration
  ← @ HEAD a1213e2 · 7 wave-2/6 agents in flight

§I THE-13-AXES (canonical · per coherence_engine.csl)
  ⟦
    0  AXIS_REALITY        ← grounded ↔ illusion
    1  AXIS_MEMORY         ← remembered ↔ forgotten
    2  AXIS_CHOICE         ← chose ↔ defaulted
    3  AXIS_SOVEREIGNTY    ← self-determined ↔ controlled
    4  AXIS_CURIOSITY      ← explored ↔ avoided
    5  AXIS_COMPASSION     ← helped ↔ ignored
    6  AXIS_CRAFTSMANSHIP  ← refined ↔ shortcut
    7  AXIS_TRUTH          ← honest ↔ deceptive
    8  AXIS_CONSENT        ← asked ↔ presumed
    9  AXIS_CONTINUITY     ← committed ↔ abandoned
    10 AXIS_RECIPROCITY    ← gave-back ↔ took-only
    11 AXIS_BEAUTY         ← beheld ↔ overlooked
    12 AXIS_MORTALITY      ← honored-death ↔ denied-death
  ⟧
  W! AXIS_COUNT = 13 (compile-time-guarantee)
  W! VALUE-RANGE [-100, 100] · NEUTRAL=0 · SENTINEL_UNKNOWN=-128

§I WHY-13-AXES-MATTER (Apocky-vision-correctness)
  ⟦
    1. coherence-engine is THE moral-ledger for the labyrinth
    2. every player-action moves along ≥1 axis
    3. NPCs · entities · scenes carry 13-axis-fingerprints
    4. procgen-output should encode 13-axes per-crystal/per-entity
    5. KAN-bias currently has 8 axes ; could be extended to 13 (or kept-as-substrate-axes-separate)
    6. substrate-render Crystal could carry 13-axis-tag for non-blocky color/intensity-modulation
  ⟧

