§I INTEGRATION-PATH (small-steps · each-non-overlapping-with-flying-agents)
  ⟦
    STEP 1 (Rust-side mirror · ~50 LOC)
      Create cssl-host-coherence-axes-13/ crate ↦ pub const AXIS_REALITY: u32 = 0 ; ... etc
      Single-source-of-truth-still-CSSL ; Rust-mirror is GENERATED-COMMENT-marked
      pub fn axis_label(id: u32) -> Option<&'static str> ← debug/log
      Tests : 13-axes-stable + count-equals-13 + label-for-each-axis

    STEP 2 (KAN-bias-extension OR sibling-array)
      Option A : extend KAN_BIAS_MULTIBAND from [5][8] → [5][13]
        ↳ format-version 0x02→0x03 with v2-back-compat-reader
      Option B : add separate static COHERENCE_AXES_VECTOR : [AtomicI32; 13]
        ↳ leaves KAN-bias undisturbed · simpler integration
      RECOMMENDATION : Option B (less-disruption · KAN-bias is statistical · coherence-axes are moral · keep separate)

    STEP 3 (Crystal-field 13-axis-tag)
      Crystal struct gets new field : axis_tag: u8 (0..=12)
      Default = 0 (AXIS_REALITY) for back-compat
      shell_world_pos can map shell-id → axis_tag (Inner=REALITY/SOVEREIGNTY/TRUTH ; Middle=COMPASSION/CRAFTSMANSHIP/etc)
      WGSL kernel could modulate per-crystal color via axis_tag (non-blocky · field-modulation)

    STEP 4 (procgen-pipeline IntentSemantic)
      ProcgenOutput.crystals carries axis_tag from intent-semantic-mapping
      DM-specialist proposes (axis_tag, intensity) tuples per ProposeAction
      role_council aggregates 13-axis-vector across specialist-decisions

    STEP 5 (display-layer modulation · LoA-aesthetic-canon-compliant)
      substrate_compose.wgsl reads per-crystal axis_tag
      maps axis_tag to color-tint-vector (chromatic-axis-association)
      e.g. AXIS_REALITY → grounded-earth · AXIS_BEAUTY → iridescent ·
            AXIS_TRUTH → clarity-white · AXIS_MORTALITY → memento-mori-bronze
      ¬ blocky · ¬ palette-painted-on-cube · IS field-data driving raymarched-color
  ⟧

